summary: Day 7. Favorite type of Pokemon? While electric types are a close second, still, I have to listen to my heart fam.  FAIRIES....
body:
Day 7. Favorite type of Pokemon?

While electric types are a close second, still, I have to listen to my heart fam.


FAIRIES.

Fairy types, ultimately.  A lot of my favorite pokemon ever are fairy types, and I just… really, really love this typing okay.  I’ve always loved fae-lore and magical things to begin with, so XY introducing this type was just a huge boon to me that left me grinning like an idiot.  Also lmao fucking finally a typing that helped balance out dragon types, good lord.  And in the rare event that I’m ever on Pokemon Showdown (lmao i’m a filthy casual don’t expect much if we ever battle, heads up) I usually just dick around on the mono tier with my team of trolltastic fairies.  My fairies have made people rage quit, man.

SO YEAH, I just really really really love my sparkly magical babies that are often written off because ‘lol too CUTESY’ but can actually fuck your shit up if you piss them off, okay.  Like, if you’ve ever read deeper into fairy lore, you’ll see what I mean.

blog.name: friendsafariserver
blog.title: Friend Safari!
blog.description:
Friend Safari is a SFW, OC-friendly, paragraph-style roleplay server for main series Pokémon games. From Kanto to Alola, the whole Pokémon world is your Cloyster! Members of this server are allowed a total of four played characters, with at least one required to be canonical.

The server is run by a team of five mods who you can learn more about via the mods page. We cultivate an easygoing and open atmosphere, with member comfort and happiness being our top priority.

All of the links are in the drop down menu under Rowlet, labeled Pokémon! Hovering over each Pokémon will tell you what page they link to!

summary: A couple relatives of mine are considering a career as Pokémon professors. What kind of degrees/experiences/skills would you...
question: A couple relatives of mine are considering a career as Pokémon professors. What kind of degrees/experiences/skills would you recommend they look into?
answer:
A degree in biology is definitely a requirement (you shouldn’t ONLY do that one, though). Volunteer work with Pokemon can help too, and to become an official professor you’ll have to pass an exam. Hope that helps!

- Professor Sakura
